PREAMBLE

SecureForge is a system hardening tool built to help individuals and
organizations protect their Linux systems. This license is designed to keep the
software free and open, encourage responsible security research, and explicitly
prohibit use of this software as a weapon against others.

Security tools are inherently dual-use. This license draws a clear line: you
may use SecureForge to defend systems you own or have explicit written
authorization to protect. You may not use it, or derivatives of it, to attack,
surveil, or harm others.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

SECTION 1 — DEFINITIONS

"Software" refers to SecureForge, including all source code, scripts,
configuration files, documentation, and associated materials distributed under
this license.

"You" refers to any individual, organization, or entity exercising rights
granted by this license.

"Authorized System" means a computer system, server, or device that you own
outright, or for which you hold current, explicit written authorization from the
legal owner to perform security configuration and hardening.

"Derivative Work" means any work that is based on, incorporates, or is derived
from the Software, including modifications, translations, ports, and integrations.

"Contributor" means any individual or entity that submits code, documentation,
or other material to the Software.

